    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, nvim does not jump into the space between two pipes with `vi|` or `ci|`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim allows for `vi|` / `ci|` motions for zig files.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There was an old Vim patch for `im{char}` / `am{char}` textobjects: https://groups.google.com/g/vim_dev/c/pZxLAAXxk0M/m/yJUpMdblI2EJ\n\n@jamessan updated it at one point, but it wasn't merged yet:\n\n- https://github.com/vim/vim/pull/958\n\nAnyways, that's how this would be implemented, so you can do `vim|` / `cim|`.",
